# Agentic Research App — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Python 3.11+ with type hints everywhere
- Anthropic Claude SDK (raw tool use, no frameworks)
- Pydantic v2 for all data models and config
- ChromaDB for vector storage
- pytest + DeepEval for testing

## Conventions
- Use Protocol classes for external dependencies (SearchProvider, EmbeddingProvider, VectorStore)
- Use pydantic-settings for environment config (not python-dotenv)
- Use `output_config.format` for structured outputs (NOT deprecated `output_format`)
- Use async/await for I/O-bound operations (httpx, API calls)
- Wrap all external API calls with retry + exponential backoff
- Return structured error results on tool failures (never crash the agent loop)
- Wrap web content in `<retrieved_content>` XML tags
- Keep functions under 50 lines — extract when larger
- Structure imports: stdlib → third-party → local (isort order)

## File Patterns
- Source code: `src/`
- Providers (external deps): `src/providers/`
- Domain configs: `src/domains/`
- Tests: `evals/`
- Reports output: `reports/`

## Testing
- Framework: pytest + pytest-asyncio + DeepEval
- TDD: write failing tests FIRST, then implement
- Mock external APIs, never mock Pydantic validation
- Run: `python -m pytest evals/ --tb=short -q`
